In the guest section, Railway’s William Moturi won on 34 points with Golf Park’s Diana Mbuba claiming the ladies title with an impressive score of 39 points, well ahead of T. Ndivo on 36 points. Winning the nines were Colin Nzioka of Limuru and David Kimanthi, both with 22 points each. Ben Murimi and S.W. Ndolo won the longest drive, while winning the nearest to pin was David Kimanthi.
Speaking during the prize giving ceremony, ICEA Lion General Business CEO, Paul Muthaura, thanked Eastern region residents and club members in particular for supporting the company’s products.
“We will walk with you all the way, and I am hoping to see you in the rest of the events in the series in Thika Greens, Ruiru, Nanyuki, Nandi and Nyali.Many of you have our golf policy and we are here to make it easy to access those services," said Muthaura.
Mary Kundu
At Limuru Country Club, Ida Njogu carded an excellent 43 points to win the Directors, Lady Captain Year Opener sponsored by Keroche Breweries, where Steve Koigi beat Stanley Kariuki on countback with 40 points to emerge the men winner.



