John Ndiho claimed the third prize with 39 points as Patricia Wangongu on 38 beat Priscilla Waithaka by one point to claim the ladies first prize. Wairimu Maina was third on 36 points and the nines went to Samurel Ngaruiya on 21.
Leading the guests was Jane Wambui on 37 points, while David Onyonka won the nearest to pin and the longest driver winners were John Gathu and K. Gachaga, while Jane Kimani was the nearest to pin lady winner, with Jane Wambui emerging the guest winner on 37 points. The Sponsors' winner was David Irimu who posted 37 points.
At Nyali Golf and Country Club, Susan Stokes posted 37 points to win the Lady Captain’s (Mary Kandu) prize by one point from Mary Kinaro. Grace Karanja finished third on 35 points, while in fourth place was Lena Breitner on 34 points. The guest winner was Mercy Nyanchama from Vet Lab Sports Club with 34 points.
She won by two points from Gladys Mutisya and Nancy Wairimu.



